metadata.documentation:
Systems Manager Incident Manager is an incident management console designed to help users mitigate and recover from incidents affecting their Amazon Web Services-hosted applications. An incident is any unplanned interruption or reduction in quality of services.

Incident Manager increases incident resolution by notifying responders of impact, highlighting relevant troubleshooting data, and providing collaboration tools to get services back up and running. To achieve the primary goal of reducing the time-to-resolution of critical incidents, Incident Manager automates response plans and enables responder team escalation.

members.documentation:
An optional field that Incident Manager uses to ENFORCE AcceptCode validation when acknowledging an page. Acknowledgement can occur by replying to a page, or when entering the AcceptCode in the console. Enforcing AcceptCode validation causes Incident Manager to verify that the code entered by the user matches the code sent by Incident Manager with the page.

Incident Manager can also IGNORE AcceptCode validation. Ignoring AcceptCode validation causes Incident Manager to accept any value entered for the AcceptCode.

AcceptPage.description: The following accept-page operation uses an accept code sent to the contact channel to accept a page.
AcceptPage.title: To accept a page during and engagement

ActivateContactChannel.description: The following activate-contact-channel example activates a contact channel and makes it usable as part of an incident.
ActivateContactChannel.title: Activate a contact's contact channel

CreateContact.description: The following create-contact example creates a contact in your environment with a blank plan. The plan can be updated after creating contact channels. Use the create-contact-channel operation with the output ARN of this command. After you have created contact channels for this contact use update-contact to update the plan.
CreateContact.title: To create a contact

CreateContactChannel.description: Creates a contact channel of type SMS for the contact Akua Mansa. Contact channels can be created of type SMS, EMAIL, or VOICE.
CreateContactChannel.title: To create a contact channel

DeactivateContactChannel.description: The following ``deactivate-contact-channel`` example deactivates a contact channel. Deactivating a contact channel means the contact channel will no longer be paged during an incident. You can also reactivate a contact channel at any time using the activate-contact-channel operation.
DeactivateContactChannel.title: To deactivate a contact channel

DeleteContact.description: The following delete-contact example deletes a contact. The contact will no longer be reachable from any escalation plan that refers to them.
DeleteContact.title: To delete a contact

DeleteContactChannel.description: The following delete-contact-channel example deletes a contact channel. Deleting a contact channel ensures the contact channel will not be paged during an incident.
DeleteContactChannel.title: To delete a contact channel

DescribeEngagement.description: The following describe-engagement example lists the details of an engagement to a contact or escalation plan. The subject and content are sent to the contact channels.
DescribeEngagement.title: To describe the details of an engagement

DescribePage.description: The following describe-page example lists details of a page to a contact channel. The page will include the subject and content provided.
DescribePage.title: To list the details of a page to a contact channel

GetContact.description: The following get-contact example describes a contact.
GetContact.title: Example 1: To describe a contact plan

GetContact.description: The following get-contact example describes an escalation plan.
GetContact.title: Example 2: To describe an escalation plan

GetContactChannel.description: The following get-contact-channel example lists the details of a contact channel.
GetContactChannel.title: To list the details of a contact channel

GetContactPolicy.description: The following get-contact-policy example lists the resource policies associated with the specified contact.
GetContactPolicy.title: To list the resource policies of a contact

ListContactChannels.description: The following list-contact-channels example lists the available contact channels of the specified contact.
ListContactChannels.title: To list the contact channels of a contact

ListContacts.description: The following list-contacts example lists the contacts and escalation plans in your account.
ListContacts.title: To list all escalation plans and contacts

ListEngagements.description: The following list-engagements example lists engagements to escalation plans and contacts. You can also list engagements for a single incident.
ListEngagements.title: To list all engagements

ListPageReceipts.description: The following command-name example lists whether a page was received or not by a contact.
ListPageReceipts.title: To list page receipts

ListPagesByContact.description: The following list-pages-by-contact example lists all pages to the specified contact.
ListPagesByContact.title: To list pages by contact

ListPagesByEngagement.description: The following list-pages-by-engagement example lists the pages that occurred while engaging the defined engagement plan.
ListPagesByEngagement.title: To list pages to contact channels started from an engagement.

ListTagsForResource.description: The following list-tags-for-resource example lists the tags of the specified contact.
ListTagsForResource.title: To list tags for a contact

PutContactPolicy.description: The following put-contact-policy example adds a resource policy to the contact Akua that shares the contact and related engagements with the principal.
PutContactPolicy.title: To share a contact and engagements

SendActivationCode.description: The following send-activation-code example sends an activation code and message to the specified contact channel.
SendActivationCode.title: To send an activation code

StartEngagement.description: The following start-engagement pages contact's contact channels. Sender, subject, public-subject, and public-content are all free from fields. Incident Manager sends the subject and content to the provided VOICE or EMAIL contact channels. Incident Manager sends the public-subject and public-content to the provided SMS contact channels. Sender is used to track who started the engagement.
StartEngagement.title: Example 1: To page a contact's contact channels

StartEngagement.description: The following start-engagement engages contact's through an escalation plan. Each contact is paged according to their engagement plan.
StartEngagement.title: Example 2: To page a contact in the provided escalation plan.

StopEngagement.description: The following stop-engagement example stops an engagement from paging further contacts and contact channels.
StopEngagement.title: To stop an engagement

TagResource.description: The following tag-resource example tags a specified contact with the provided tag key value pair.
TagResource.title: To tag a contact

UntagResource.description: The following untag-resource example removes the group1 tag from the specified contact.
UntagResource.title: To remove tags from a contact

UpdateContact.description: The following update-contact example updates the engagement plan of the contact Akua to include the three types of contacts channels. This is done after creating contact channels for Akua.
UpdateContact.title: To update the engagement plan of contact

UpdateContactChannel.description: The following update-contact-channel example updates the name and delivery address of a contact channel.
UpdateContactChannel.title: To update a contact channel
